item.title: “The Acute Effects of Varying Intensities of Treadmill Walking Exercise on Cognition in Persons with Multiple Sclerosis”
item.description:
Brian Sandroff will be holding his PhD final defense on Wednesday, May 20th at 9 A.M.

Location:  128 Freer Hall

The dissertation title is "The Acute Effects of Varying Intensities of Treadmill Walking Exercise on Cognition in Persons with Mulitiple Sclerosis"

All faculty, staff and students are invited to attend.
